This graph shows the progress of three cohorts from Std IV to Std VIII. For example, the first cohort was in Std IV in 2008, in Std VI in 2010, and in Std VIII in 2012. For this cohort: % children who could do division in Std IV (in 2008) was 15.2%, and in Std VI (in 2010) was 35.2%. When the cohort reached Std VIII in 2012, this figure was 55.2%. The progress of each of these cohorts can be understood in the same way.

